clinical_study.brief_title: Evaluation of Stenfilcon A Versus Etafilcon A
clinical_study.official_title: Evaluation of Stenfilcon A Versus Etafilcon A

detailed_description.textblock: One week dispensing, investigator-masked, randomized, contralateral study comparing the test lens against the control lens. Each subject will be randomized to wear the test lens in one eye and the control lens in the other eye simultaneously.

primary_outcome.description: Participants rated their comfort of lenses by subjective questionnaire (un-annotated scale, 0-100, 0=Poor comfort/intolerable, 100=Excellent comfort/cannot be felt) Change over time measured at insertion, After settling, 12-hours, 1-week

Participants rated dryness of the lenses by subjective questionnaire (annotated scale, 0-100, 0=cannot be worn / extremely dry, 100=no dryness experienced at any time) Change over time measured at 12-hours, 1-week

primary_outcome.measure: Participant's Subjective Rating of Lens Handling for Insertion (Questionnaire)
primary_outcome.description: Participants rated their lens handling experience for lens insertion by questionnaire (un-annotated scale, 0-100, 0=could not place lens on eye, 100=always easy to place lens on eye) Measured at Dispensing

primary_outcome.measure: Participant's Subjective Rating of Lens Handling for Removal (Questionnaire)
primary_outcome.description: Participants rated their lens handling experience for the lens removal by questionnaire (un-annotated scale, 0-100, 0=could not remove lens from eye, 100=always easy to remove lens from eye) Change over time measured at 12-hours, 1-week

primary_outcome.measure: Participant's Subjective Rating of Visual Quality (Questionnaire)
primary_outcome.description: Participants rated visual quality of the lenses by questionnaire (annotated scale, 0-100, 0=extremely poor vision all of the time. Cannot function, 100=excellent vision all of the time) Change over time measured at 12-hours, 1-week

primary_outcome.measure: Participant's Subjective Rating of Overall Preference (Questionnaire)
primary_outcome.description: Participants rated their overall lens preference by questionnaire. (annotated scale, 0-100, scale normalized to 0=no preference, +50=strongly prefers test lens, -50=strongly prefers control lens). Change over time measured at 12-hours, 1-week

secondary_outcome.measure: Investigator's Objective Assessment of Lens Surface Wettability (Biomicroscopy)
secondary_outcome.description: Investigators assigned a lens surface wettability grade by biomicroscopy assessment (grading scale, 0 to 4, 0=excellent, 4=severely reduced). Change over time measured after lens settling (insertion), after 12-hours wear on the dispense day (12-hours), after a minimum on one hour of lens wear at 1 week (1-week).

secondary_outcome.measure: Investigator's Objective Assessment of Overall Fit Acceptance (Biomicroscopy)
secondary_outcome.description: Investigators assigned an overall fit acceptance grade by biomicroscopy assessment (grading scale, 0-4, 0=very poor, 4=very good). Change over time measured at insertion, 12-hours, 1-week

secondary_outcome.measure: Investigator's Objective Assessment of Visual Acuity, High Contrast at High Illumination (Snellen)
secondary_outcome.description: Investigators tested participants using snellen charts distant to the participant in each eye (monocular) at normal lighting conditions (high illumination). (logMAR, 0.00 = 20/20 Snellen acuity, positive values = poorer visual acuity, negative values = better visual acuity). Change over time measured at insertion, 12-hours, 1-week.

secondary_outcome.measure: Investigator's Objective Assessment of Visual Acuity, High Contrast at Low Illumination (Snellen)
secondary_outcome.description: Investigators tested participants using snellen charts distant to the participant in each eye (monocular) at low lighting conditions (low illumination). (logMAR, 0.00 = 20/20 Snellen acuity, positive values = poorer visual acuity, negative values = better visual acuity). Change over time measured at insertion, 12-hours, 1-week.

secondary_outcome.measure: Investigator's Objective Assessment of Anterior Ocular Physiological Response, Cornea (Biomicroscopy)
secondary_outcome.description: Investigators assigned an anterior ocular physiological response grade by biomicroscopy assessment with corneal staining (grading scale, 0-4, 0=none, 4=severe) Change over time measured at baseline (screening and dispensing visit), 12-hours, 1-week

secondary_outcome.measure: Investigator's Objective Assessment of Anterior Ocular Physiological Response, Conjunctiva (Biomicroscopy)
secondary_outcome.description: Investigators assigned an anterior ocular physiological response grade by biomicroscopy assessment with conjuncitval staining (grading scale, 0-4, 0=none, 4=severe) Change over time measured at baseline (screening and dispensing visit), 12-hours, 1-week

The sponsor cannot require changes to the communication and cannot extend the embargo.
